e tax loop holes still exist. When I got hired they had a nice retirement specialist talk to us. Guess what one of the things they talked about. Investing money in tax free buisnesses that you can then claim for tax losses if they fail.</span></div></blockquote><br />So your opinion is entirely based on some vague memory of a newbie seminar on investing?  That would explain it.</div>

			

